# Rust build output. Lands at culex/.cargo/target/ when CARGO_TARGET_DIR is
# set in the nix shell, and at src-tauri/target/ for some invocations — the
# unrooted pattern catches both.
target/

# Generated by `cargo tauri android init` / `cargo tauri ios init`. Contains
# the full Xcode + Gradle projects. Some teams check these in so signing
# configs / build settings are versioned; we don't, yet. Revisit when CI
# signing is wired up.
#
# Exception (committed via `git add -f`, not via a !-pattern here because
# gitignore can't re-include from an excluded dir cleanly): a few resource
# files we hand-customize for app identity — LaunchScreen.storyboard,
# Info.plist, themes.xml, colors.xml, ic_launcher_background.xml,
# AndroidManifest.xml. Once tracked, git follows their changes despite this
# ignore.
src-tauri/gen/

# Firebase client config — identifies the project, ships embedded in every
# APK so not a hard secret, but kept out of the repo so the Firebase
# project ID isn't pinned to source history. Already implicitly ignored
# via src-tauri/gen/ above; listed explicitly in case that pattern changes.
src-tauri/gen/android/app/google-services.json

# Frontend bundle. For the spike, the webview loads hivegame.com remotely
# and dist/index.html is just a fallback. Once we move to a bundled CSR
# Leptos build, dist/ will be populated by cargo-leptos and should stay
# ignored (build output, not source).
dist/*
!dist/index.html

# macOS Finder noise
.DS_Store
